Obsidian vault for {{USER_NAME}} ({{USER_ROLE}}{{COMPANY:+ at {{COMPANY}}}}).

## Retrieval System (Engram-inspired)

**Never read the entire vault.** The retrieval system uses hierarchical lookup inspired by the "Conditional Memory via Scalable Lookup" paper (DeepSeek Engram). Scale layers sequentially, stop as soon as resolved.

### Boot (auto-loaded by SessionStart hook)
- `MEMORY.md` (memory index, auto-loaded by Claude Code memory system)
- Daily Note for today (create if missing; check current state and pending items)
- `00-Dashboard/hot-cache.md` (Tier 1+2 notes, injected by session-scan.sh)

### Layer 1: Deterministic Lookup (O(1), on demand)
- `00-Dashboard/concept-index.md` (hash table: concept -> notes)
- `00-Dashboard/aliases.md` (term normalization/synonyms for query expansion)

### Layer 2: Filtered Search (when Layer 1 didn't resolve)
- Define **context vector** (domain, project, phase) before searching
- `<folder>/index.md` (navigate by structure)
- `grep` filtered by domain/type, max 5 results

### Layer 3: Semantic Search (last resort)
- Smart Connections MCP, max 3 results
- Only when grep returns empty AND concept isn't in the index

### Retrieval Budget: max 20% context window for retrieval, 80% for reasoning.

## Vault Structure

```
00-Dashboard/          # Entry point, weekly review, dashboards
10-{{PRIMARY_DOMAIN}}/  # Primary work domain
30-Content/            # Content production
40-Partnerships/       # Partnership CRM (1 note per partner)
50-Events/             # Speaking, events, conferences
60-Research/           # Trends, references, industry analysis
70-People/             # Contact network (1 note per person)
80-Templates/          # Templates for each note type
85-Rules/              # Code rules, workflows, dev patterns
90-Archive/            # Completed/archived items
99-Inbox/              # Staging area for raw material
Daily-Notes/           # Daily journal (YYYY-MM-DD.md)
MOCs/                  # Maps of Content (thematic navigation)
```

## Maintenance Rules

1. **Create/delete a file** -> update `index.md` in the folder
2. **Every new note** -> complete YAML frontmatter (see below)
3. **Descriptive names**: `2026-03-04 Partnership Meeting TechCorp.md`, not `meeting.md`
4. **Atomic notes**: 1 idea, 300-500 words, self-contained
5. **Archive** -> move to `90-Archive/`, update both index.md files

## Required Frontmatter

```yaml
---
title: "Descriptive title"
summary: "One sentence summarizing the content"
type: concept | project | reference | meeting | daily | moc | template | person | event | decision | error-solution | devlog | toolbox | knowledge | hub
domain: {{DOMAINS}}
tags: []
status: draft | active | evergreen | paused | completed | archived | superseded | deprecated
created: YYYY-MM-DD
---
```

`summary` is REQUIRED. It's what the agent scans before reading the full file.

## File Format

- `[[wikilinks]]` for internal links
- `[text](url)` for external URLs
- `> [!type]` for callouts
- Tags: `#tag` or `#nested/tag`

## Vault Automation Commands

| Command | What it does | When to use |
|---------|-------------|-------------|
| `/start` | Intelligence briefing + Daily Note | Start of day |
| `/recap` | Summary of today so far (read-only) | Any time |
| `/end` | Summarize day + decisions + tomorrow | End of day |
| `/health` | Vault health audit | Part of /weekly or on demand |
| `/weekly` | 7-day review | Monday |
| `/dump` | Brain dump with auto-routing | Any time, free-form thinking |
| `/capture` | Interactive guided note capture | End of work session |
| `/process` | Process material into atomic notes | After research |
| `/scan` | Scan files modified outside vault | Start of session |
| `/connections` | Discover cross-domain links | Part of maintenance |
| `/link-check` | Insert missing wikilinks in recent notes | After creating notes |
| `/contrarian` | Check for excessive agreement, unverified facts | Part of /weekly |

## Cross-Domain Connections

When creating or updating notes:
1. Search for **cross-domain** connections (research <-> content <-> events <-> work)
2. Add bidirectional wikilinks
3. Highlight productive tensions between domains (these are content hooks)

## Large File Reading

When reading any file, if you suspect it may have >2000 lines, use `offset` and `limit` to read in chunks. The Read tool has a silent limit of 2000 lines per call. For large files:
1. Check the size first: `wc -l <file>`
2. If >2000 lines, read in chunks of 1500 using `offset` and `limit`
3. Never assume a single read captured the complete file

## Tools

- **Obsidian MCP** (read/write notes)
- **Smart Connections MCP** (semantic search, Layer 3 of retrieval)
